18072835885953521;1751970509;“A Thin Layer of Light”

Don’t be fooled by the lines of my shoulders,
or by the posture that doesn’t tremble.
It’s only armor —
a thin layer of light
beneath which lives someone
who still hasn’t learned
how to ask for tenderness without shame.

I touch the world with caution,
as if each day could shatter.

I don’t shout.
I listen,
though often no one speaks to me truthfully.

Is it weakness —
to want to be seen
without a role,
without demands,
without needing to impress?

Is it naïve —
to dream that someone might embrace
not my triumphs,
but the moments I stay silent too long?

My soul is not made of steel,
though many would like it to be.
It is parchment,
on which the night writes its questions.

Can one be strong
while longing for only this:
that someone might say you are
and want nothing changed?

At times,
I believe the hardest part to play
is a man
who needs no more proof —
only to love
and be loved
without the curtain.;59526820125;sophiadanae903
